        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I like the idea about the anti-regen spell.  However, I do forsee a potential downside to using the spell (other than potential aggro and whatnot), during certain fights such as Itraer Vius IV.</P><P>For those that do not know who this is, its a HUGE robed looking guy that resides in Akheva.  The reason why the type of spell could have a double edge is if one fails against mobs such as this.</P><P>The reason being is that IV the IV is a rooted boss mob.  Once he has taken damage he, like most high end mobs will summon.  Since he is rooted, you have to fight right under him (can't pull him to a safe spot).  If you fail, you would have to wait till he regens ALL of his HP back before you can proceed with the clean up.  Even if you zone out, the moment you get on his aggro list, you are summoned and beat.  Not really sure how large his aggro range is, but this can take upwards of 30 mins for him to regen.  I guess you could summon the corpes back to the zone, however the fight back to him and the setting up agian would require much longer time and cost way too much.  </P><P>Adding this type of spell to the mix would just make the wait much longer.  However, I still would support a spell like this just because it would increase the chances of success.  Just stating something potentially to be aware of so no one would find out the hard way and start to bitch and whine <img src=icon_smile.gif border=0 align=middle>.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=191272" target="_blank">Merkurion Everdeth</a><BR>=--60 Warlock of The Rathe--=<BR>Member of <a href="http://66.205.128.39/" target="_blank">Tindi' Losi</a></P><P>"Get busy living, or get busy dying" -The Shawshank Redemption<BR></font></td>
