di as an example like i always do:  Your guild has been trying to kill vindi and keep getting close but can't quite get it, with this spell you should now be able to get him that little bit you have been missing.  however, if your guild couldn't even get vindi below 60% before, this spell isn't going to enable you to beat him now.</P><P>as for the, but this will only have one necro wanted on a raid...shaman are in the same boat; you only need 1 there to slow.  but most guilds will want a few back ups, so figure atleast 2 necro's on a raid...and figure a guild will want a few extra necro's in case those 2 aren't on.  personally, i see it as a way for necro's that previously couldn't get guilds to perhaps have a better chance.</P><P>this spell won't trivialize things anymore then slow does...and nothing comes close to touching what the CH cycle has done to the game.</P><P><a href="http://www.theinverselogic.com/" target="_blank"><BR>Abillister "Monkey" Abu<BR>Inverse Logic</a></font></td>
