        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Etadanik Mistmorgue</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Well, since we don't have flat numbers, we know nothing if it'd be overpowering or, worse, underpowering.  For example, does any necro here use our strength-deduction line (not the group tap)? Anyone use Trucidation or Infusion? No.  Why? Because the spells are broken.  If monster regen is far lesser, or far greater, than we presumed it to be, then yes, this spell could be broken as well.</P><P>Now if VI sees this and believes they could implement it without under or overpowering the spell, I'm all for it.  Given the lack of numbers on monster regen, however, there are simply too many variables at stake for me to believe that this spell is easily feasible.  I'm not saying it's a bad idea, but that for it to be a feasible idea, there must be facts to back it up.  <BR>    <BR>Alot of ideas would be "nice": why not a spell that reduces mob damage? Why not a spell that makes mobs *miss* 50% of the times? Why not a spell that vastly reduces a mob's AC so tanks hit for 30% more damage? All could be potentially useful, but the thing is they are *new* ideas, which means adding a whole new line of spells in the game, and as such they require a HUGE justification on our part.  Modifying existing spells is easy, and doesn't really upset the existing balance of the game.  But adding something new is *always* potentially destructive.  Look at the paladins, for example, and their "silence" line that had to be completely nerfed b/c of its devastating effects.  It's been my experience that EQ has a tendency to sway towards opposite sides - either a spell is too powerful (Slow, CH) or it's worthless (lots of candidates here).  Making a spell "just right" is difficult, and even more so when you don't have any facts to back it up.  That's why I responded skeptically.  If we had some facts to work with, it could prove interesting to try and find a balanced spell line to possibly present to VI, but otherwise, there's really not much we can do except mention it as a possibility, like the hundreds of other ideas we've seen on this board over the past years.</P><P><BR>Etadanik the Redeemed</font></td>
      </tr>
