        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> people have listed the hard numbers on mobs regens (well the numbers that certain 3rd party programs give anyways).  if someone actually cares enough to do a search of some boards i'm sure they are there (safehouse, allakhazam, etc...).  i know i've seen solid numbers on mobs in the past, just aside from their HP i never paid much attention.</P><P>but we know mobs with 150,000 HP must have some form of decent regen while fighting because...if you had just 5 melee doing max hits of 50, it would take only 10 minutes to kill a 150k mob.  most raids have around 30-40 people, and they tend to do more then just 50pts a hit...obviously what you said about not knowing if it will be overpowered or underpowered is present...personally, i believe as long as long as they (VI, the people with hard numbers) take a look at mobs regen's on a general basis then a balanced % of regen reduction can be created. </P><P>the 20% i listed probably is a bit much and it should be closer to 10%, but i figured i'd rather ask for more and then compromise by going less.  by asking for something that is semi realistic but a bit above it; and then compromising you get the number to what we actually wanted.  if we asked for 10%, we would probably have to end up with 5% (assuming the spell idea is even considered that is).</P><P><a href="http://www.theinverselogic.com/" target="_blank"><BR>Abillister "Monkey" Abu<BR>Inverse Logic</a></font></td>
